Teva Surges Most in 10 Months After Advancing in U.S. Trade

-- B y   G w e n   A c k e r m a n
-- 
2011-10-02T15:05:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-02/teva-surges-most-in-10-months-after-advancing-in-new-york-trade.html
Teva Pharmaceutical Industries Ltd. (TEVA) 
soared the most in 10 months following advances in New York
trading.  The shares gained 5.7 percent, the biggest increase since
Dec. 9, to 140.70 shekels, the equivalent of $37.53, at the 4:30
p.m. close in  Tel Aviv . The U.S.-traded shares closed at $37.22
on Sept. 30 after gaining 5 percent while the Israeli market was
closed for a Jewish holiday.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Gwen Ackerman in Jerusalem at 
 gackerman@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Susan Lerner at 
 slerner2@bloomberg.net  